# Build scratch — neither is committed.
#
# The MCP server is shipped as SOURCE only. The runnable artifact is a native
# executable produced on the end user's machine by `bun build --compile`
# (see build.sh). A compiled binary is platform-specific, so it CANNOT be
# committed; it is built on-device, lazily, on first use.
node_modules/

# dist/ holds the local-dev / CI compile output (`mise run build-task-mcp`).
# The on-device build writes to ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA}/bin instead.
dist/
